channel.title: Proxychains/Tor help needed
channel.description:
Hi, I am trying to add socks5 proxy after tor exit node. I have set the proxychains.conf correctly and set tor to transparent proxy setting, however when proxychains starts it appears to ignore the .conf file and say 127.0.0.1 9050 denied.
Proxychains works through iceweasel but not Tor, been trying for 2 days now, any help would be greatly appreciated.
Cheers

item.title: Proxychains/Tor help needed
item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
jackmulligan:

If I use iceweasel in the workstation through proxychains do I stile have Tor protection?

Yes, but not Tor Browser’s protections. ( https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Tor_Browser )

item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
No progress has been made.

Does currently not work. Someone needs to contribute by figuring this out. Otherwise this will not be possible for a very long time.

For the record., related documentation chapter:

Whonix – 18 Jun 19

Connecting to Tor before a Proxy

Instructions on how to connect to Tor before a proxy (User → Tor → Proxy → Internet)

item.title: Proxychains/Tor help needed
item.dc:creator: onionfields
item.description:
It has worked for me before by using 9951 (in accordance with the socks5 client) with a dynamic chain. socks4 is commented out of course. perhaps try 9951 for a port instead or perhaps 9950, 9051, etc

item.title: Proxychains/Tor help needed
item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
Be warned. This will be very difficult to fix. Even bug report will be difficult.

You’re getting this error, I suppose?

|DNS-request| www.torproject.org 
dig: /home/user/tor-browser_en-US/Browser/TorBrowser/Tor/libcrypto.so.1.0.0: no version information available (required by /usr/lib/libdns.so.88)
06-Jan-2015 21:23:26.402 ENGINE_by_id failed
06-Jan-2015 21:23:26.403 error:25066067:DSO support routines:DLFCN_LOAD:could not load the shared library:dso_dlfcn.c:187:filename(/home/ubuntu/install/openssl/lib/engines/libgost.so): /home/ubuntu/install/openssl/lib/engines/libgost.so: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory
06-Jan-2015 21:23:26.403 error:25070067:DSO support routines:DSO_load:could not load the shared library:dso_lib.c:244:
06-Jan-2015 21:23:26.403 error:260B6084:engine routines:DYNAMIC_LOAD:dso not found:eng_dyn.c:450:
06-Jan-2015 21:23:26.403 error:2606A074:engine routines:ENGINE_by_id:no such engine:eng_list.c:418:id=gost
dig: dst_lib_init: crypto failure
|DNS-response|: www.torproject.org is not exist

I am quite sure this is some issue with proxychains and/or some lib and/or Tor Browser and not caused by Whonix.

If you want to go through the jungle of technical issues, try find out if and which fork of proxychains is still maintained and make a very good question / bug report. See my signature for guidance. Sorry to say, but since I am very busy with other Whonix work, I can’t be a big help here.

Read full topic
